snippet.textDisplay: To deal with the bubbles early on, abscond with your girlfriend's (boyfriend? whatever turns you on...) favorite vibrator. Turn it on, obviously, and place it on the table near the curing gels. It will only need a minute or two usually; less if you're into weapons-grade Hitachi Magic Wands. Of course, you'll need the surface to cooperate, so some super sturdy workbench may not transfer the vibration enough. It really does not take too much vibration to get excellent results tho. Be courteous, thoroughly clean, obviously, and replace the batteries & return the vibrator where you found it. It helps to make a mental note and/or picture to aid in dispelling any suspicion that the magical little device may have been used for some pseudo-nefarious purposes. You may wish to toss in an unexpected surprise candle-light dinner at her favorite restaurant just to complete the covert op with some extra distraction.

snippet.textDisplay: might freeze drying work? if you had water in the gel instead of methanol you could potentially gently freeze it into a solid block of ice (this could cause cracking but it might be possible to avoid this) then you place it under a strong vacuum and the water sublimes off. it's also possible to freeze dry mixtures of acetonitrile and water which might be better as organic solvents don't expand when they freeze like water does.
